Preheat your oven to 180°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for the
@Small Sweet Potato{2}. Take the @Pork Medallion{4} out of your fridge so it
can come to room temperature. Peel the sweet potato and chop into roughly 2cm
cubes. Chop the @Broccoli{2} into florets. Crush the @Black Peppercorns{1} in a
#pestle and mortar{}.

> TIP: If you don't have a pestle and mortar you can put them in a freezer bag
> and whack them with a rolling pin!

Season the pork with a good pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Put a
drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the pork
and cook until it is nicely browned, ~{2%minutes} on each side.

Transfer the pork to a #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven
for ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: Don't wash the frying pan as we'll use it to make the sauce later.
> TIP: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, take the pork out of your oven, cover loosely with #foil{} and leave
it to rest for a few mins.

Cook the sweet potato in your pan of boiling water until soft, ~{10-15%minutes}.
Once done, fish it out with a #slotted spoon{} and keep the water boiling for
the broccoli. Put the sweet potato in a #mixing bowl{} and mash with a
#potato masher{}. Season with salt and black pepper and stir through a knob of
@?butter{} or @creme fraiche{1%tbsp}.

Put the saucepan of water you used for the sweet potato back on medium-high heat
and bring to the boil (top it up if necessary). Add the broccoli and cook until
tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{}, reserving some water for your
sauce.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat. Add the reserved
@Water{300%ml}. Stir in the @Beef Stock Pot{1} and crushed peppercorns. Simmer
until reduced by half. Take off the heat and set aside for ~{2%minutes}, then
stir in the @Creme Fraiche{1}. Slice the pork and serve with the broccoli,
sweet potato mash and peppercorn sauce. Enjoy!